WEBVTT

00:10.000 --> 00:22.000
You're Watching on 123Movies.to

00:36.720 --> 00:39.280
- Morning, Mister.
- Morning, young man.

00:44.000 --> 00:46.275
Who are you trying to impress?

00:46.400 --> 00:48.231
Tell that boy
to put the paper in the door.

00:48.400 --> 00:50.789
Or next time
it'll be a big bottle.

01:02.200 --> 01:04.839
In the nose, out the mouth.
In the mouth, out the nose.

01:05.120 --> 01:08.157
Don't breathe. Now breathe in.
And hold it in!

01:08.640 --> 01:12.030
Confuse that body, rattle it!
Make it crazy!

01:12.480 --> 01:14.948
Hold it, hold it.

01:15.840 --> 01:17.512
Ziya, Hayrettin, Kadir.

01:17.680 --> 01:20.194
Stand like this
or your spleen will blow up.

01:24.240 --> 01:27.710
Look at Saffet the teacher there.
What a saint.

01:28.040 --> 01:30.235
See? He's rounded up
the poor duckies again...

01:30.440 --> 01:33.591
And got them Eid outfits.
Bless him, the dear.

01:33.720 --> 01:36.188
But he knows all
about walking on the road.

01:36.680 --> 01:37.715
Hey, teacher!

01:38.640 --> 01:39.755
Ýsmail Abi.

01:40.280 --> 01:42.794
You're hogging the road
like cattle.

01:43.120 --> 01:45.350
Am I supposed to
whip you into line?

01:45.720 --> 01:47.711
And you say you've seen the city.

01:48.200 --> 01:50.714
There's only one Sivas, son.

01:51.040 --> 01:52.553
Anything you want to learn
is here.

01:53.960 --> 01:55.518
- Where are you going?
- To the village.

01:55.760 --> 01:58.638
OK, that's on our way.
Bye then. See you.

02:01.080 --> 02:02.877
Move over there.

02:15.480 --> 02:19.553
It's the same every Eid, Fikret.
You oversleep, we have pray outside.

02:20.480 --> 02:23.153
My roots needed a fix, Ýsmail Abi.

02:38.400 --> 02:39.753
Here, brethren.

02:41.320 --> 02:43.993
Have some shame,
it's a holy morning.

02:44.520 --> 02:46.636
Don't drive me to sin please.

02:46.840 --> 02:50.719
This fridge box is foreign.
I'm not prostrating myself on it.

02:51.080 --> 02:53.275
God forgive you!

02:53.480 --> 02:57.473
Çetin Abi, spare me today of all days.
Turn it over, you won't see the logo.

02:59.920 --> 03:01.911
Fikret abi, hear that?
He's talking logos.

03:02.480 --> 03:04.948
Ýsmail Abi, excuse me
while I shit on him.

03:05.680 --> 03:07.398
Not a single mat left, huh?

03:08.080 --> 03:09.513
Çetin, Çetin!

03:10.280 --> 03:12.669
- What's up?
- I'm fine, praise God. You?

03:12.960 --> 03:15.076
I was preaching
before you bust in, Çetin.

03:15.280 --> 03:18.033
On the rules and virtues
of Eid prayers.

03:18.160 --> 03:20.196
You always do the same sermon.

03:20.360 --> 03:23.716
So what?
He figured we hadn't got it.

03:24.040 --> 03:27.555
Çetin, enough! Sit down.
You whine every Eid. How many now?

03:28.040 --> 03:29.189
- Three!
- And you're cocky.

03:29.360 --> 03:30.349
Never!

03:30.840 --> 03:33.877
Don't get me wrong, imam.
You collected a ton of alms.

03:34.080 --> 03:37.356
OK, call it my sin.
But where did those alms go?

03:37.640 --> 03:40.791
On air-con,
on wall-to-wall carpets.

03:41.000 --> 03:42.479
Zip it, teacher!

03:42.840 --> 03:46.230
You're like a punch-hungry wimp
trying to break up a fight.

03:46.400 --> 03:49.312
But you're talking to the imam.
Manners, please!

03:49.800 --> 03:54.078
Honoured imam, it's come to my notice
that you have no spare mats.

03:54.360 --> 03:57.352
My worthy brothers must pray
on whatever they find.

03:57.640 --> 04:00.552
Fikret Abi had 'for sale'
printed on his forehead last Eid.

04:00.840 --> 04:02.478
He got the ads page.

04:02.720 --> 04:06.713
3 beds, lounge, new kitchen/bath
in Þarkýþla. Monthly fees 80 lira.

04:07.440 --> 04:08.429
For your attention!

04:08.600 --> 04:10.591
Enough, Çetin!
OK, I'm starting.

04:10.880 --> 04:12.916
Get chanting, Hüseyin.
Quick!

04:27.840 --> 04:31.310
Give whatever you can.
God will reward you in heaven.

04:32.480 --> 04:34.596
Eid blessings, Abi.
Have some cologne.

04:35.840 --> 04:37.717
Give whatever you can.

04:37.960 --> 04:39.075
Eid blessings, Abi.

04:39.480 --> 04:40.469
Friend.

04:41.000 --> 04:43.798
This is from five of us,
but we need change.

04:43.960 --> 04:45.234
But this is change!

04:45.800 --> 04:47.028
I'll keep it then.

04:48.520 --> 04:51.114
Give what you can,
help out the mosque.

04:54.440 --> 04:56.476
Give what you can.

04:57.720 --> 05:00.393
Help out the mosque.
Give what you can.

05:01.920 --> 05:03.353
This sucks.

05:03.680 --> 05:06.956
Even the alms box is
a foreign bleach box, huh?

05:07.080 --> 05:09.548
God forgive you!
Çetin Abi, don't bother.

05:09.680 --> 05:11.079
Get a receipt, brothers.

05:11.240 --> 05:13.515
Get a receipt.
No one's getting a receipt.

05:14.600 --> 05:17.797
Çetin, why not make peace
with your village imam?

05:18.120 --> 05:20.998
Go to Eid prayers there
if you don't like this mosque.

05:21.080 --> 05:23.594
Anyway it's less crowded there.

05:23.720 --> 05:26.393
I'm not at war,
just making a stand.

05:28.960 --> 05:32.396
Beat it! Tell your dad
to pay his debt from 2004.

05:32.840 --> 05:34.068
And he celebrates Eid!

05:39.360 --> 05:40.475
Eid blessings!

05:47.160 --> 05:48.912
Put this in your pocket.

05:49.480 --> 05:52.313
Wake up, Nazmi Amca.
I'm Fikret, the gas man.

05:52.720 --> 05:54.039
He's got old, Çeto.

05:54.160 --> 05:56.435
- What are you sacrificing?
- A bit of skirt!

05:56.920 --> 06:00.754
C'mon, it's the end of Ramadan,
not the Feast of the Sacrifice.

06:01.240 --> 06:02.719
God, he's got old.

06:02.880 --> 06:06.077
Chill, Fikret Abi. He's a big giver.
Here, Nazmi Amca. Eid blessings!

06:06.280 --> 06:07.429
Eid blessings!

06:09.400 --> 06:10.435
- Tank?
- Dad!

06:10.640 --> 06:12.073
Son!

06:12.520 --> 06:14.875
Tank!
What are you doing here?

06:15.160 --> 06:18.072
- Nothing wrong, huh?
- No, dad. Thought I'd surprise you.

06:18.280 --> 06:21.636
Come here then
and let me hug you. Son!

06:28.800 --> 06:32.475
Saffet, when did you sneak in?
I'm stuck on Tank's lap here.

06:33.120 --> 06:36.999
I'll swap if you like, Fikret Abi.
I'm his godfather, I'm OK.

06:37.200 --> 06:38.189
What does that mean?

06:38.320 --> 06:41.198
- Marriage is a no-no.
- What does that mean?

06:41.360 --> 06:44.909
Nazmi Amca, when did you sneak in?
Where are you going?

06:45.120 --> 06:46.712
Is Yýldýzeli on the way?

06:48.640 --> 06:53.589
Tank, I once spent a fortune to get
half as zoned out as Nazmi Amca.

06:54.640 --> 06:56.756
Here's the fare for five people.

06:57.120 --> 06:58.348
He's paying for us too.

06:58.680 --> 07:01.433
What is this, Nazmi Amca?
Shame on you!

07:01.800 --> 07:05.315
Forget fares. Come with us
and have a good breakfast at ours.

07:05.400 --> 07:06.992
I'll drop you off later.

07:08.560 --> 07:10.312
<i>It was my first time back in years.</i>

07:10.880 --> 07:14.077
<i>It feels incredible
when someone goes wild just to see you.</i>

07:15.240 --> 07:20.394
<i>What's going on, Mum? It's only me.
What’s so amazing about that, Dad?</i>

07:21.080 --> 07:24.470
<i>My precious boy!
How I'd die for you!</i>

07:24.600 --> 07:27.751
<i>You know, there are people here
who love you more than anyone else.</i>

07:28.000 --> 07:29.274
You're all maniacs!

07:29.480 --> 07:32.358
<i>It's not the place you miss
but the people in it.</i>

07:32.640 --> 07:34.551
OK, don't hit my boy.
He's my boy.

07:34.720 --> 07:36.517
Go on in, dear.
You must be hungry.

07:36.800 --> 07:40.031
<i>You're treated to the best food
in the best place.</i>

07:40.240 --> 07:42.310
<i>Just because you've come home.</i>

07:42.440 --> 07:45.671
<i>People race around
to make you feel at home.</i>

07:45.840 --> 07:47.398
Whose son are you?

07:49.160 --> 07:50.195
Huh?

07:52.120 --> 07:53.189
Ahmet's.

07:53.280 --> 07:54.998
That father of yours...

07:55.640 --> 07:57.870
He was a nasty piece of scum.

07:58.760 --> 07:59.795
The check!

08:06.000 --> 08:09.879
<i>Missing these people you love
suddenly becomes missing the city.</i>

08:11.400 --> 08:15.552
<i>And I'd arrived that day to give
these lovely people a little surprise.</i>

08:21.880 --> 08:24.758
Look, son.
I'm not the narrow-minded type, OK?

08:24.960 --> 08:28.316
Hell no, I've an open mind.
I'll say that.

08:28.480 --> 08:31.836
Marry if you like.
I'd never interfere. Why should I?

08:32.200 --> 08:35.828
But I need some background.
Who is this girl, who's her family?

08:36.080 --> 08:38.991
Marika and I worked for the same firm
in Latvia. Then...

08:39.120 --> 08:40.109
I don't want to know!

08:40.320 --> 08:44.029
Why this thing fora foreign bride?
Are all Sivas girls blighted?

08:44.480 --> 08:46.948
Look, it's his life.
What's it to us?

08:47.280 --> 08:50.750
What do you mean?
I can't even say the girl's name!

08:51.160 --> 08:54.072
She's our bride, not some stranger.
For heaven’s sake!

08:54.360 --> 08:56.715
So listen.
Where was Latvia a district of?

08:57.280 --> 08:58.713
3 hours by air from Istanbul.

08:59.040 --> 09:02.589
Capital, Riga. Maritime climate,
humid, harsh winters.

09:04.440 --> 09:06.158
Ýsmail Abi,
is the girl Muslim?

09:07.000 --> 09:09.878
What's it to you
if she is or not, Fikret?

09:10.480 --> 09:13.597
If he slammed Fikret Abi,
she isn't Muslim, boys.

09:13.720 --> 09:14.755
Slammed?

09:15.000 --> 09:18.595
Muslim or not, what's it to you?
They're in love. What's it to us?

09:18.960 --> 09:20.075
- Ýsmail Abi.
- What?

09:20.280 --> 09:23.511
"To you" to him and "to us" to him...
What's bugging you?

09:23.600 --> 09:25.750
The Latvia project is over now.

09:25.960 --> 09:27.996
So they want Marika in Italy,
me in Turkmenistan.

09:28.160 --> 09:31.391
For us to stay in the same country
means marrying PDQ.

09:31.640 --> 09:32.755
- In Timbuktu?
- Huh?

09:32.920 --> 09:35.275
- In Timbuktu?
- No, pretty damn quick.

09:36.240 --> 09:37.468
Poof-poof, poof-poof.

09:37.920 --> 09:39.558
Poof-poof, Çeto. Poof-poof.

09:39.840 --> 09:41.114
He caught us on the hop.

09:41.680 --> 09:44.911
If I'd known before,
I'd have got the money I'm owed...

09:45.320 --> 09:46.878
And done the wedding.

09:47.040 --> 09:48.473
We've been ambushed.

09:49.680 --> 09:52.956
Who can we ask for money
when it's Eid?

09:54.120 --> 09:57.112
We've eaten from every hand, Ýsmail.
Count our blessings!

09:57.880 --> 09:59.996
Don't go bowing and scraping again.

10:00.440 --> 10:01.429
F*ckaduck.

10:01.840 --> 10:04.274
- What's the fuss about, Ýsmail?
- What?

10:04.440 --> 10:07.716
The boy's worked abroad for years.
He must have savings.

10:07.880 --> 10:10.110
- Let him do the wedding.
- Now look!

10:13.840 --> 10:17.071
Look, son. A real father with us
has his son circumcised...

10:17.360 --> 10:21.831
Sends him to school, then the army
and gets him married. It's our way.

10:21.960 --> 10:27.637
I won't have this village accuse me
of not giving my son a wedding!

10:27.840 --> 10:30.308
If we have 10 days,
I'm doing this wedding.

10:30.520 --> 10:32.476
Dad, we'd planned
on something simple.

10:32.680 --> 10:34.477
Planned on what?
Is it your wedding?

10:34.760 --> 10:37.228
It's my wedding now!
That's my job.

10:37.440 --> 10:40.637
Now you tell me about Latvia,
the weather and all that.

10:40.800 --> 10:42.153
OK, Dad. If you say so.

10:42.400 --> 10:45.915
I say, friends,
we'll do this wedding in 10 days.

10:46.160 --> 10:48.435
Hah! I knew
you'd go round in circles...

10:48.560 --> 10:50.516
And end up
palming us off with the job.

10:52.920 --> 10:57.072
Ýsmail Abi, when you said 10 days
I figured you knew something.

11:00.000 --> 11:02.560
He does!
What kind of friends are you?

11:02.640 --> 11:04.835
He slammed Tank
because he trusted us.

11:06.840 --> 11:09.149
What's 'slam', Çeto?
It's on my brain now.

11:09.680 --> 11:12.752
<i>Fikret Abi gets fired up
faster than anyone you ever saw.</i>

11:12.960 --> 11:17.192
<i>Dad claims Fikret Abi runs on gas,
so he often calls him Gas Man Fikret.</i>

11:17.520 --> 11:21.911
<i>Fikret Abi is all words and no action.
A man of impulse. He runs a gas store.</i>

11:22.040 --> 11:23.109
Hello!

11:23.680 --> 11:24.635
Yes?

11:25.320 --> 11:26.309
No.

11:26.920 --> 11:27.909
Maybe.

11:28.440 --> 11:29.429
Get out of here!

11:29.600 --> 11:33.309
<i>He's also a bit rash.
He lost two wives to cancer.</i>

11:33.440 --> 11:36.477
<i>After his first wife died
he decided not to marry again.</i>

11:36.760 --> 11:39.115
<i>But he soon reneged
and remarried.</i>

11:39.360 --> 11:41.749
<i>He can keep a cool head
come what may.</i>

11:41.960 --> 11:43.837
<i>Fikret Abi never panics.</i>

11:50.520 --> 11:53.830
<i>Come here, boy.
C'mon, c'mon, in here.</i>

11:54.160 --> 11:55.115
Come here, c'mon.

11:55.480 --> 11:57.118
Look at the place!

11:57.440 --> 12:00.113
There's a leak.
The place stinks of gas.

12:00.280 --> 12:03.078
I have a cig on the go.
It'll get ugly. What is this?

12:03.560 --> 12:05.312
Sweep the place. Now!

12:06.080 --> 12:07.433
Tut-tut-tut.

12:10.680 --> 12:13.478
You want us on the main news, huh?

12:14.440 --> 12:15.634
Bünyamin.

12:16.120 --> 12:18.270
Tell your dad
to pay his gas debts.

12:18.680 --> 12:22.434
<i>So it was Fikret Abi
who was first to stand by Dad.</i>

12:22.680 --> 12:24.272
We'll do the wedding, Ýsmail Abi.

12:24.520 --> 12:27.512
Your son is mine.
I'll handle the venue.

12:27.680 --> 12:29.796
The wedding will be
at the Sivas Hotel.

12:29.920 --> 12:32.070
C'mon, Fikret Abi!
The place costs a fortune.

12:32.240 --> 12:34.708
I'll fix that.
Just leave it to me.

12:34.880 --> 12:37.189
What's your contribution?
Let's hear it!

12:37.360 --> 12:38.395
OK.

12:38.560 --> 12:41.677
I'll do the lemonade, cake,
spoons, the bridal convoy...

12:42.040 --> 12:44.395
And however many cars there are...

12:44.520 --> 12:46.875
All the ribbons for the wing-mirrors...

12:47.080 --> 12:49.150
Whether on the left or right.
Ýsmail Abi...

12:49.520 --> 12:53.195
The Prophet said help newlyweds.
I'll do the wedding outfits too.

12:53.960 --> 12:55.359
Mum can make them.

12:55.760 --> 12:58.911
Çetin, it's 5 years
since your mum was a tailor.

12:59.080 --> 13:01.230
OK, but would she let down her son?

13:01.640 --> 13:06.670
Çeto, your mum's blind.
Blind as a bat. That's why she quit.

13:07.920 --> 13:11.276
Çetin, we put your mum on a wage
so she'd quit, right?

13:11.800 --> 13:13.836
We do a whip-round every month, right?

13:14.040 --> 13:16.270
If I say I'll handle it,
I'll handle it.

13:16.600 --> 13:17.555
OK?

13:17.840 --> 13:18.909
OK?

13:19.120 --> 13:20.189
OK?!

13:20.440 --> 13:22.749
Çetin Abi was
a latecomer to the gang.

13:23.320 --> 13:26.073
The gang was his escape
from the loser crowd.

13:26.160 --> 13:29.869
He was wild in his youth.
He even demanded protection money.

13:30.240 --> 13:33.118
He drank heavily.
Got in a coma a few times.

13:33.280 --> 13:35.669
One day he was hammered again.

13:35.880 --> 13:38.440
<i>So badly it was dawn
when he found his way home.</i>

13:38.640 --> 13:39.993
But there was no one home.

13:40.240 --> 13:43.550
The neighbours said
his dad was catching a bus to Mecca.

13:43.720 --> 13:46.678
He ran to find his dad,
but could barely stand up.

13:46.800 --> 13:48.279
Stand up! You shame me.

13:48.480 --> 13:50.835
You aren't my son!

13:51.040 --> 13:53.952
Nothing had hurt Çetin Abi
until then. Until those words.

13:54.080 --> 13:57.436
What did it mean,
"You aren't my son!"?

14:10.840 --> 14:13.115
That night he dreamed of a mullah.

14:15.200 --> 14:17.919
So your father said
you weren't his son.

14:18.520 --> 14:21.432
There's only one thing to do then.

14:21.880 --> 14:23.199
I'll do anything, mullah.

14:23.320 --> 14:26.869
Only one thing for me to do,
not you.

14:27.000 --> 14:28.069
Hold this.

14:37.200 --> 14:38.269
Oh my God!

14:38.560 --> 14:40.790
Oh my God, oh my god!

14:47.040 --> 14:49.918
Who knows if he really was beaten
by the mullah?

14:50.200 --> 14:52.475
But Çetin Abi was changed
after that night.

14:52.640 --> 14:54.278
"It's over," he said.

14:54.800 --> 14:58.349
He never drank again.
He began to get his life in order.

15:01.520 --> 15:05.274
The poor give all, the rich just money
as they say, teacher.

15:05.760 --> 15:06.875
OK then.

15:07.200 --> 15:10.795
As Tarik is a friend,
as everyone's being selfless...

15:11.880 --> 15:14.155
I'll bring a musical diva,
I'll bring Emel Sayýn.

15:14.400 --> 15:16.994
Right. Her absence is felt.

15:17.600 --> 15:20.353
So Emel Sayýn wasn't
at my first circumcision...

15:20.640 --> 15:24.110
And the knife slipped.
That explains most of my problems.

15:24.480 --> 15:25.549
Sit down!

15:28.640 --> 15:31.393
Oh my God!
That's hysterical.

15:32.040 --> 15:36.113
They said they'd bring in
Roberto Carlos to head SivasSpor.

15:36.440 --> 15:38.590
That cracked me up
as much as this.

15:38.800 --> 15:39.835
But then they did.

15:39.960 --> 15:41.552
You shouldn't laugh at everything.

15:41.640 --> 15:44.313
Sivas has become something else.

15:44.560 --> 15:47.233
It's like I fight with Roberto
for parking spaces.

15:47.440 --> 15:50.637
But our wedding’s more Arabesque,
more Selami Þahin.

15:50.960 --> 15:52.154
- Really?
- Yes.

15:52.440 --> 15:55.193
I'm more into Doðan.
Latif Doðan, 'I'm Miffed'.

15:55.560 --> 15:56.709
Hah.

15:56.840 --> 15:57.989
It's more folksy.

15:58.280 --> 16:02.239
Fine, but they'd want a fortune.
Emel is family. If I ask, she'll come.

16:02.440 --> 16:03.634
It takes one call.

16:03.920 --> 16:05.672
She's my dad's aunt's cousin!

16:05.840 --> 16:11.075
To his aunt, to his aunt I lost my heart
It's rare you find a teacher half as smart.

16:13.560 --> 16:16.120
OK, bum deal,
we'll go for Emel.

16:16.960 --> 16:18.154
And if we find the money...

16:19.280 --> 16:21.475
We'll swap her for someone else.

16:22.080 --> 16:23.115
You make me laugh.

16:23.440 --> 16:26.716
Saffet Abi teaches primary school.
He's crazy for the job.

16:28.120 --> 16:31.112
He went to free boarding school
so feels he owes the state.

16:32.800 --> 16:35.917
Who knows how many villagers
he taught to read and write?

16:36.080 --> 16:39.038
He was last to join the gang.
It's a mystery how he did.

16:39.160 --> 16:42.072
If he's ever accused of lying,
it freaks him out.

16:42.440 --> 16:43.793
Why would I lie?

16:44.000 --> 16:46.355
She's my aunt's cousin.
Don't make me crazy!

16:46.480 --> 16:47.515
Drop it.

16:47.640 --> 16:52.270
At least my spin's half-believable.
The cake, lemonade, ribbons.

16:52.680 --> 16:56.389
The hotel owner's an army buddy.
He was at my barracks.

16:56.680 --> 16:58.910
We're like grandpa and grandson.
I'm grandpa.

16:59.200 --> 17:02.112
But his aunt's grandpa.
You figure that out!

17:04.760 --> 17:07.433
We're back here tomorrow night then.

17:07.800 --> 17:09.199
Dad had done it again.

17:09.400 --> 17:11.789
He'd made a decision
and roped in his friends.

17:12.000 --> 17:15.709
Call it charm or persuasion,
that was Dad's nature.

17:15.880 --> 17:16.915
Ýsmail!

17:17.200 --> 17:19.667
I was looking for you.
They said you were here.

17:19.920 --> 17:22.877
Here's your share.
Enjoy!

17:23.240 --> 17:24.468
God bless you.

17:25.640 --> 17:28.029
So no one stopped him
sacrificing the beast.

17:28.319 --> 17:29.355
That's too bad.

17:29.640 --> 17:31.995
Fora morsel of meat
they kept quiet.

17:32.440 --> 17:35.034
Nazmi Amca, is the hide
going to the mosque?

17:35.360 --> 17:38.318
There was no hide.
Not much hide this year.

17:38.920 --> 17:39.955
Don't eat that meat!

17:40.240 --> 17:41.639
Who knows what it is?

17:42.000 --> 17:42.989
Don't eat it.

17:43.400 --> 17:45.231
I'll ask the mukhtar
if anyone's missing.

17:45.400 --> 17:46.628
OK, God bless.

17:47.120 --> 17:48.189
Right.

17:48.520 --> 17:49.714
God bless.

17:50.720 --> 17:54.030
ÇETIN ABI IS NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR LOST (STOLEN) PROPERTY.

17:54.160 --> 17:55.229
HE'S A REFORMED MAN.

18:00.800 --> 18:02.313
Where have you been, Ýsmail?

18:02.520 --> 18:03.669
Oh my God!

18:05.560 --> 18:06.549
What time is it?

18:06.960 --> 18:09.838
I was just at the teahouse
with friends.

18:10.560 --> 18:13.836
The teahouse again, huh?
What kept you till this hour?

18:13.920 --> 18:15.558
It's your son’s fault.

18:15.720 --> 18:18.109
We're skint.
The boys and I are working on it.

18:18.520 --> 18:20.715
Let the boy
do the wedding himself.

18:21.280 --> 18:24.272
Your son's giving you these ideas,
isn't he?

18:24.520 --> 18:29.071
I see! He's your son
during school and the army...

18:29.280 --> 18:32.033
My son when it doesn't suit you, huh?
Well think again!

18:32.320 --> 18:36.472
Look, if you want to do that wedding,
stop being a mule...

18:36.560 --> 18:38.278
...and ask your brother for the money.

18:38.440 --> 18:40.112
I don't have a brother!

18:42.280 --> 18:43.235
Got tha...

18:44.280 --> 18:45.349
Hatice?

18:46.000 --> 18:47.149
Hatice.

18:47.400 --> 18:49.311
Where are you?
I'm scared of the dark.

18:53.560 --> 18:55.949
<i>Baby, when Dad said that,
what could I do?</i>

18:56.560 --> 18:57.629
Thanks.

18:57.880 --> 19:00.030
Dad talked about the Sivas Hotel.

19:00.280 --> 19:02.953
But it's not definite yet.

19:42.920 --> 19:44.148
Selam aleykum!

19:44.840 --> 19:46.956
Whoa! A valet, huh?

19:47.320 --> 19:49.231
Hey, park the truck somewhere decent.

19:49.480 --> 19:53.075
No cruising or you're screwed.
I know the mileage. Here.

19:53.760 --> 19:54.875
Nice catch.

19:55.560 --> 19:58.233
Oaf!
Don't make the lady carry it.

19:58.400 --> 19:59.674
She's your mum's age.

20:01.680 --> 20:03.033
Hah!

20:14.400 --> 20:15.469
Made for each other.

20:15.600 --> 20:16.555
Can I help?

20:16.640 --> 20:20.349
Hello. It's years since I saw
such a picture of beauty, ma'am.

20:20.840 --> 20:22.558
That's why it won't come out.

20:22.760 --> 20:23.715
She's embarrassed.

20:24.760 --> 20:26.671
It's stuck in my mouth.

20:27.000 --> 20:28.592
- What do we do?
- How can I help?

20:28.680 --> 20:31.069
I just put the swankiest hello
you'll ever see...

20:31.400 --> 20:34.119
Right here.
First take it.

20:34.320 --> 20:35.594
Sir, let me help.

20:35.720 --> 20:37.278
Beat it!
Don't piss me off!

20:37.880 --> 20:41.350
Give me a tent in an earthquake
and I'd still sleep outside!

20:43.880 --> 20:45.313
My brown beauty, my rose.

20:45.480 --> 20:47.391
I even use brown sugar in my tea.

20:47.840 --> 20:48.989
You ha...

20:49.200 --> 20:50.315
Yes, officer?

20:50.600 --> 20:51.828
Who are you after?

20:52.040 --> 20:53.473
Who am I after? Umm...

20:53.840 --> 20:58.152
Young black-tache Sirn of Adýyamanlý.
Good-timer Sirn. The hotel owner.

20:58.360 --> 20:59.554
Who are you?

20:59.720 --> 21:01.756
Who? Say Grandpa Fikret.
Gas man Fikret.

21:02.040 --> 21:04.634
But he won't know what I do
in ciwy street.

21:05.480 --> 21:06.674
Say Gunner Fikret.

21:07.000 --> 21:08.479
I was a gunner in the army.

21:09.520 --> 21:10.475
Now go!

21:12.040 --> 21:14.679
Where were we
before he interrupted?

21:15.560 --> 21:16.788
Where are you going?

21:17.240 --> 21:19.754
You chased her away.
God damn you!

21:20.040 --> 21:22.156
Yes, you! You aren't my type.
Beat it!

21:24.680 --> 21:28.229
<i>Hello? Sir, your grandfather,
Gunner Fikret is here.</i>

21:29.080 --> 21:30.035
Who?

21:30.240 --> 21:31.832
<i>Your grandfather,
Gunner Fikret.</i>

21:31.880 --> 21:34.952
Is this a joke?
What grandfather? What gunner?

21:35.520 --> 21:37.715
Don't you know
my grandfathers are dead?

21:37.920 --> 21:39.717
I was confused too, sir.

21:39.920 --> 21:41.239
<i>He said he's a gas man.</i>

21:41.320 --> 21:42.275
A gas man?

21:42.360 --> 21:43.998
- Yes.
- Idiot!

21:44.320 --> 21:46.436
Who needs deliveries?
We use mains gas...

21:46.600 --> 21:48.272
<i>- At this hotel!
- Sorry, sir.</i>

21:48.480 --> 21:50.596
I'll stop bothering you.
Goodbye.

21:51.080 --> 21:53.958
Aren't the tourism guys here?
It's a holiday dammit.

21:54.040 --> 21:55.473
No, just the gas man.

21:56.200 --> 21:57.553
Still the gas man.

21:58.080 --> 21:59.035
Hang up!

22:01.040 --> 22:02.075
Fikret Bey.

22:02.200 --> 22:04.475
Yes, officer?
Is there some mistake?

22:04.600 --> 22:08.229
No, but Sirn Bey is busy.
He'll see you later.

22:09.360 --> 22:11.828
See you in an hour.
I'll drop off my orders.

22:13.640 --> 22:15.756
Ýsmail, I say...

22:16.000 --> 22:19.913
We do a dead simple, no-frills wedding.
I talked to Tank.

22:20.160 --> 22:23.630
He said, "Don't bust a gut for me.
I don't need a party. "

22:24.160 --> 22:26.469
We already discussed this, Missus.

22:26.680 --> 22:28.432
It's all taken care of.

22:28.880 --> 22:31.838
We're doing a team effort.
You stay out of it.

22:32.400 --> 22:33.628
That's my job.

22:34.240 --> 22:38.119
Look, Fikret...
Is talking to the Sivas Hotel.

22:39.120 --> 22:41.953
So we'll soon be
all over the Sivas Post.

22:42.040 --> 22:43.314
- Is that it?
- Well now.

22:43.440 --> 22:45.908
Fikret is right out of his depth.

22:46.320 --> 22:49.596
His wife borrowed money last month.
She still hasn't paid me back.

22:49.720 --> 22:52.632
She just says Fikret is owed,
but he can't ask for it.

22:53.080 --> 22:57.198
Well, she's right.
I owe Fikret a bit.

22:57.480 --> 23:00.040
So look, I owe Fikret a bit.

23:00.920 --> 23:03.673
His wife owes my wife a bit.

23:03.920 --> 23:06.388
It's a mighty mess.
Does Çetin have money?

23:06.520 --> 23:07.873
- Çetin?
- Yes.

23:07.960 --> 23:09.473
What's he doing?

23:11.400 --> 23:13.994
Not getting his mum
to make the wedding dress?

23:17.520 --> 23:19.078
His mum's blind, right?

23:22.440 --> 23:24.192
My sides will split.

23:24.320 --> 23:25.799
God willing.

23:27.960 --> 23:30.030
Do you mean that, Ýsmail?

23:31.880 --> 23:34.474
Where are you going?
Your breakfast. Ýsmail!

23:34.760 --> 23:35.795
Whoa!

23:37.840 --> 23:38.955
Oh my God!

23:39.720 --> 23:40.789
Oh my God!

23:41.760 --> 23:44.035
Oh my God!
Who put that there?

23:45.160 --> 23:47.310
Go get...
wise in the ways of God.

23:48.320 --> 23:49.469
Stay focused.

23:49.680 --> 23:51.511
Stay focused!
Everyone here!

23:56.800 --> 23:58.756
Put love into that punch.

23:58.960 --> 24:00.791
The aim is not
to beat up your opponent.

24:00.880 --> 24:02.108
It's to bring him into society.

24:02.240 --> 24:04.674
Remember, put love into it.
What's up?

24:05.120 --> 24:06.394
Remember, put love into it.

24:06.480 --> 24:09.040
Punch his soul, not his body.
Smile.

24:09.280 --> 24:11.748
Smile
so he smiles back.

24:13.040 --> 24:15.793
I fought 61 matches
as a pro boxer.

24:16.000 --> 24:18.878
That's 58 knockouts in a row.
I lost.

24:19.400 --> 24:21.868
A two-win streak escaped me.
I never forget.

24:22.000 --> 24:25.515
I promised myself I'd quit boxing
if I won the next fight.

24:25.720 --> 24:26.914
I won that fight.

24:27.040 --> 24:31.875
No punch will make you unhappy.
Because no one unhappy can change the world.

24:32.040 --> 24:34.429
A 61 license plate is from Trabzon.
A58?

24:34.560 --> 24:35.515
Sivas!

24:35.600 --> 24:39.040
So why can't another Olympic
champion come out of this class?

24:39.040 --> 24:40.393
Another Hamza Yerlikaya!

24:40.760 --> 24:42.273
You two, over there.

24:42.840 --> 24:44.068
C'mon, move!

24:44.600 --> 24:47.990
Anyone late with fees
trains on the fridge today.

24:48.240 --> 24:52.518
OK, a standard punch bag
is good for 65,000 punches.

24:52.680 --> 24:55.069
I'm not wasting it on you.
Now get training.

24:57.880 --> 24:58.869
Mum, Mum?

24:59.560 --> 25:00.913
Watch your friends.

25:01.160 --> 25:02.195
Mum, Mum!

25:02.480 --> 25:03.435
Mum.

25:03.640 --> 25:05.676
Mum, I tell you what.

25:07.320 --> 25:10.073
Classical music is over.
Nothing new comes out.

25:10.520 --> 25:14.752
Where are Baroque and the Romantics?
It's out with Bach, in with Baha.

25:15.160 --> 25:16.309
Çetin, I have no money.

25:17.200 --> 25:19.111
Mum, don't give me grief.
Look.

25:19.360 --> 25:22.716
I'm on a thin line between being
and not being. I'm invisible.

25:22.880 --> 25:24.552
Imagine.
The line's wider than me.

25:24.720 --> 25:25.948
I can't borrow.

25:26.080 --> 25:28.753
What do you mean, Mum?
I was on Voice of Sivas TV.

25:29.040 --> 25:32.396
They reported on me beating up
the boxing boys for their fees.

25:32.600 --> 25:34.556
If the governor hears...

25:34.760 --> 25:37.354
This place will close.
How will I get the money?

25:37.480 --> 25:38.959
I've no more gold.

25:39.200 --> 25:40.519
Oof!

25:41.120 --> 25:42.109
Really?

25:42.400 --> 25:44.960
Sit quietly now.
Ýlyas, back to your place!

25:45.960 --> 25:49.555
<i>Hello? This is Saffet from Sivas.
I'm a cousin...</i>

25:49.920 --> 25:51.035
Of Emel Sayýn.

25:51.240 --> 25:53.913
<i>Say Gürbüz Ahmet’s son
and she'll know.</i>

25:57.440 --> 25:59.317
Give me your number.

25:59.680 --> 26:02.353
<i>Emel Haným is tied up.
I'll call when she's free.</i>

26:02.440 --> 26:03.429
OK.

26:03.560 --> 26:04.959
<i>Do you have a pen?</i>

26:05.120 --> 26:07.475
Yes.
Go ahead.

26:08.160 --> 26:09.354
- 3.
- 3.

26:09.720 --> 26:11.312
- 32.
- 32.

26:11.640 --> 26:13.278
- 16
- OK, 16.

26:14.760 --> 26:16.557
Thanks.
I'll be waiting.

26:18.080 --> 26:19.229
Play this lot.

26:21.760 --> 26:23.273
Stop!
Move back.

26:26.440 --> 26:28.670
There you go. Up!
Stand up!

26:29.480 --> 26:30.549
What did I say?

26:30.800 --> 26:34.190
What happens if you don't pay
your fees on time? This!

26:34.560 --> 26:37.791
I'll come find you
wherever you are...

26:37.960 --> 26:41.669
And get my money. It's not yours.
Now c'mon, box!

26:45.240 --> 26:46.229
Tank.

26:46.720 --> 26:48.551
How old is the bride?

26:49.280 --> 26:50.269
Same age as me.

26:54.040 --> 26:55.075
Does she speak Turkish?

26:55.240 --> 26:57.913
Well, she hears
but she can't speak it.

27:02.960 --> 27:07.954
Tarik, you're in an awful hurry
to get married, you know.

27:08.480 --> 27:11.677
Well, it gives us
all kinds of ideas, son.

27:12.040 --> 27:14.110
C'mon, out with it.
I won't be angry.

27:14.240 --> 27:15.832
But what's the question?

27:15.960 --> 27:17.632
Tell your wet nurse.

27:17.800 --> 27:19.472
What are you talking about?

27:19.560 --> 27:21.437
Did you get the girl pregnant?

27:21.720 --> 27:23.278
Answer your wet nurse.

27:23.320 --> 27:26.392
It's obvious what you'll say,
but answer the question.

27:26.680 --> 27:29.148
No, Mum. Are you crazy?
We use protection.

27:29.320 --> 27:32.437
Protection against who, what?
Why don't we know?

27:32.560 --> 27:33.595
No, not that.
Well...

27:33.800 --> 27:35.597
Protection against umm...

27:35.840 --> 27:37.114
Against what?

27:40.680 --> 27:42.432
Oh my!
Let's go.

27:42.600 --> 27:44.352
This boy is bad.

27:45.160 --> 27:47.310
Run!
How could you say that?

27:47.400 --> 27:48.719
How could you ask that?

27:48.920 --> 27:51.992
May you be struck down by rocks
as big as me!

27:53.040 --> 27:54.109
Just like your dad.

28:01.720 --> 28:02.948
Take him away.

28:05.000 --> 28:09.073
It would be fair to say
we did this to promote tourism.

28:09.360 --> 28:13.194
Well, well, well! Sirn,
the wayward grandson. Selam aleykum.

28:13.600 --> 28:16.637
Lady, can I stick this here?
It's to go a customer.

28:17.960 --> 28:18.915
Sirn!

28:20.760 --> 28:21.875
Who are the dames there?

28:21.960 --> 28:24.394
If they were horses,
I'd stake my fortune.

28:24.520 --> 28:27.193
150 small gas bottles, 60 big,
they're worth it.

28:27.360 --> 28:31.273
Fikret, my friend.
We're in a crucial meeting here.

28:31.400 --> 28:34.073
If we can finish it,
then I'll help you.

28:34.280 --> 28:36.919
Help yourself first.
Your fly’s open.

28:37.280 --> 28:40.511
True, you should leave
the door to a dead man's house open.

28:42.160 --> 28:43.388
I found it funny.

28:44.240 --> 28:45.832
Anyway my thing's urgent.

28:46.000 --> 28:47.797
You know our Ýsmail,
the smith?

28:48.000 --> 28:49.433
His son's getting married.

28:49.760 --> 28:51.432
I say do the wedding here.
Huh?

28:51.560 --> 28:52.993
- We were discussing that.
- The wedding?

28:53.160 --> 28:54.354
No, tourism.

28:54.800 --> 28:57.872
Now that Sivas
is on the tourist map...

28:58.080 --> 28:59.433
A lot of tourists come.

29:00.720 --> 29:01.914
Let's see...

29:03.040 --> 29:04.519
We're fully booked.

29:05.760 --> 29:07.478
What do tourists want in Sivas?

29:07.760 --> 29:09.671
There's no sea, nothing.
Just a river.

29:09.800 --> 29:11.279
They'd bathe in that?

29:11.800 --> 29:13.233
Look, see her?

29:13.680 --> 29:16.399
If she were moonshine
I'd drink her neat.

29:16.480 --> 29:19.040
Fix me the dark one.
I'll down her in one.

29:19.200 --> 29:20.235
Just a second.

29:20.360 --> 29:22.191
Tourists don't come here?

29:22.280 --> 29:24.271
Of course they do, lady.

29:24.680 --> 29:26.398
- Annually at least-
- One day.

29:26.480 --> 29:28.994
Talk all you like.

29:29.200 --> 29:31.668
Look, lady.
I'm from Sivas born and bred.

29:31.920 --> 29:34.639
The tourist sights
are 2-3 hours away.

29:34.840 --> 29:38.196
It's a public holiday.
How many guests here? Zero, nix.

29:38.480 --> 29:39.469
Sirn!

29:40.960 --> 29:43.110
That dark one, OK?
If she wrote a book...

29:44.360 --> 29:45.315
I'd read it.

29:45.520 --> 29:47.556
Think, the book and me.
I tell you I'd read it.

29:47.680 --> 29:50.194
I've one industrial gas bottle,
that's yours too.

29:50.280 --> 29:54.034
- C'mon, fix it, Sirn.
- We'll handle that later.

29:54.160 --> 29:56.469
But why talk about Sivas like this?

29:56.600 --> 29:59.114
Look, we're growing.
We have a university.

29:59.880 --> 30:01.950
So Sivas is growing.
You know, growing.

30:02.120 --> 30:03.473
What, growing to you?

30:04.200 --> 30:05.679
What's the population of Sivas?

30:06.000 --> 30:08.309
623,000.
How many Sivas people in Istanbul?

30:08.480 --> 30:11.074
- 2, maybe 2.5-
- No way!

30:11.320 --> 30:13.834
3! Istanbul has
3 million Sivas people.

30:13.960 --> 30:15.996
If we don't stay here,
why would tourists?

30:16.360 --> 30:17.349
The man's right.

30:17.680 --> 30:19.591
So, partner?
We do the wedding here?

30:21.800 --> 30:22.755
OK.

30:23.200 --> 30:24.189
Hah!

30:28.600 --> 30:29.555
Fiko.

30:30.320 --> 30:31.469
Is that gas bottle full?

30:31.680 --> 30:32.829
Yes.

30:39.280 --> 30:43.114
It's tourist season at the Sivas Hotel
so they're booked up.

30:43.440 --> 30:45.192
- Sirn said so.
- Fikret!

30:45.480 --> 30:47.232
Did the bastards beat you up?

30:47.640 --> 30:50.632
- There was a small spat between us.
- Fikret Abi...

30:50.920 --> 30:53.832
Give me the bastard's name
and I'll trash his love train.

30:54.080 --> 30:56.230
Give me the name,
the name, the name.

30:56.520 --> 30:57.475
Dammit!

30:57.640 --> 31:01.838
Any guy who can beat up me,
Fikret, the gas man...

31:04.800 --> 31:06.631
He's at the Sivas Hotel, boys.

31:08.160 --> 31:11.755
But he beat me up
something else, Çeto.

31:12.160 --> 31:14.230
Twice on the way home
I forgot my name.

31:14.560 --> 31:16.437
And a few times...

31:16.520 --> 31:18.795
I didn't know where I was.
I lost the plot.

31:20.160 --> 31:21.639
Here, friend.

31:23.040 --> 31:24.393
OK, 20 lira for?

31:24.600 --> 31:25.953
Winston Light, two packs.

31:26.200 --> 31:27.952
We don't sell cigs.

31:28.440 --> 31:29.793
Some newsstand!

31:32.840 --> 31:34.831
Thanks a lot.

31:37.000 --> 31:38.353
Hey, are we moving?

31:42.520 --> 31:44.397
- How many of them?
- Huh?

31:44.840 --> 31:45.989
How many of them?

31:46.680 --> 31:49.990
OK, no slandering.
It was Sirn on his own.

31:50.120 --> 31:52.680
He bashed away at my head
with the gas bottle.

31:52.960 --> 31:56.350
Sly dog,
he gets me with my own weapon.

31:56.800 --> 31:57.755
Look.

31:58.160 --> 31:59.149
It's all dented.

31:59.320 --> 32:01.515
My customer refused to take it.

32:01.640 --> 32:03.471
Ýsmail Abi,
let me go trash the guy.

32:03.600 --> 32:06.876
First let's see to the wedding,
then Sirn.

32:07.000 --> 32:09.753
It's nothing.
Now where are you with food and drink?

32:11.160 --> 32:13.435
- When did we get to that?
- We already got there.

32:13.600 --> 32:15.636
Umm, they need cash.

32:16.080 --> 32:18.640
They need supplies, right?
They have a point.

32:19.080 --> 32:22.356
If we're stuffed on that,
I won't even ask about Emel Sayýn.

32:22.560 --> 32:23.629
- No, ask.
- Emel Sayýn?

32:23.880 --> 32:24.995
We're relatives.

32:25.520 --> 32:27.397
Doing that really bugs me.

32:27.640 --> 32:28.868
I swear she’s family.

32:29.000 --> 32:31.150
I got her manager today.
I'll call back.

32:31.320 --> 32:32.469
Teacher, zip it!

32:32.920 --> 32:35.593
Ýsmail Abi,
let's fix the cash thing ASAP.

32:36.280 --> 32:39.078
The lady took me by the arm
to the clinic.

32:39.480 --> 32:43.075
Coming back I hit on my own wife.
I talked dirty in her ear.

32:43.760 --> 32:44.988
I thought she was hot for me.

32:45.480 --> 32:50.031
I slung my wife of 7 years,
my lawful wife into a friend's house.

32:50.520 --> 32:52.192
