Now take this bag and fill it...

37:53.000 --> 37:54.479
As full as you like.

37:54.680 --> 37:57.831
These favors you do
will become legend, you know?

37:58.240 --> 38:03.155
You know what? You make me
want to stroke your spleen, I swear.

38:03.560 --> 38:06.916
Look, I'll tell Tarik
to set up a Facebook group for you.

38:07.040 --> 38:09.793
You're the pride of Sivas,
not just its jeweler.

38:10.680 --> 38:12.272
C'mon, please.

38:12.960 --> 38:15.633
Anyone else would do the same.

38:16.640 --> 38:20.315
But the thing is, I only have
27 followers on Twitter.

38:20.840 --> 38:25.709
So I'd love it if you told Tank
to do a Friday Follow to my account.

38:26.040 --> 38:27.473
I'm kind of antisocial.

38:27.640 --> 38:29.631
I don't have
Twitter or Facebook at home.

38:29.880 --> 38:32.440
But like I said,
I'll take your dick fora spin.

38:33.000 --> 38:37.596
Look, we'll find those followers
and give them hell, don't you worry.

38:38.080 --> 38:41.356
Punks! Who are they following?
This is Sivas!

38:41.560 --> 38:44.154
- It's harassment.
- We're onto it, don't worry.

38:44.840 --> 38:47.229
We'll go then
before trashing the place.

38:47.360 --> 38:49.999
Then I'll umm
give you this.

38:51.160 --> 38:53.355
Did you take a good look?

38:54.360 --> 38:56.430
Just a single quarter in there, huh?

38:56.800 --> 38:58.870
Just this, Ýsmail Abi.

38:59.000 --> 39:02.117
I'll strangle that boy like a turkey,
Ýsmail Abi.

39:02.200 --> 39:04.839
- All that talk.
- This is beyond us.

39:05.160 --> 39:08.152
And the girl's family
are on a plane.

39:08.640 --> 39:10.870
We've messed up here.

39:11.400 --> 39:13.709
Abi, don't get mad,
but I have an idea.

39:15.240 --> 39:16.958
Your brother might help.

39:17.320 --> 39:18.753
Right away if I asked.

39:19.920 --> 39:23.196
The wedding's beyond me, right?
He'd help like a shot.

39:23.600 --> 39:24.919
Time fora confab.

39:25.240 --> 39:27.390
Brethren, to the front row please.

39:28.960 --> 39:32.794
There'll be a ton of jewelry given
at the wedding. If we were to keep it...

39:33.760 --> 39:34.749
Just suppose.

39:35.560 --> 39:39.633
If we use that for our expenses,
the jewelry money will subrevize it.

39:40.280 --> 39:42.430
Subrevize?
What are you talking about?

39:42.520 --> 39:44.078
Just that, Fikret Abi.

39:44.200 --> 39:47.351
Ýsmail Abi, let's go right now
and get a loan from the bank.

39:47.560 --> 39:50.120
- The cleanest kind.
- The cleanest kind?

39:50.920 --> 39:53.195
We'll use it on the basics.

39:53.320 --> 39:56.073
We'll all get fake jewelry
to give at the wedding.

39:57.000 --> 39:58.433
So it won't cost anything.

39:58.560 --> 40:02.269
We'll pay the loan with money
from the jewelry. If we keep it.

40:02.600 --> 40:04.830
We'll keep it,
I'll see to that.

40:05.160 --> 40:06.593
So what do you say?

40:07.880 --> 40:09.199
A loan in whose name?

40:09.400 --> 40:12.073
The name of love, brotherhood,
humanity, the collective!

40:14.520 --> 40:16.715
In Ýsmail Abi's name.
Ýsmail Yücesoy.

40:16.960 --> 40:18.996
The loan will be in my name.

40:19.040 --> 40:20.359
Did you bring a pay slip?

40:20.480 --> 40:22.471
I only brought my ID.

40:22.680 --> 40:25.558
The other thing I didn't umm...
What was it?

40:25.720 --> 40:27.199
A pay slip.

40:27.280 --> 40:29.555
That's a paper
showing how much you earn.

40:29.680 --> 40:32.831
Hah, I see. I'm retired.
I'm on a pension.

40:33.040 --> 40:36.191
You can't borrow
more than a year's pension.

40:36.320 --> 40:38.151
And only from your pension bank.

40:38.200 --> 40:40.509
The loan is deducted monthly.

40:41.040 --> 40:42.871
Mention the jewelry.

40:43.000 --> 40:44.991
Now look, the thing is this.

40:45.400 --> 40:48.790
As soon as we get the jewelry
we'll pay you back.

40:49.160 --> 40:50.718
We can't lend to pensioners.

40:50.880 --> 40:52.711
Oof, I've had it.

40:53.000 --> 40:54.115
Wait, Ýsmail Abi.

40:54.240 --> 40:55.275
I'll take it on.

40:55.600 --> 40:56.953
Banker, give it to me.

40:58.000 --> 40:59.353
What do you do for a living?

40:59.720 --> 41:01.756
I'm the boss.
I run my own business.

41:01.840 --> 41:04.638
- In what?
- Unnatural gas and energy.

41:04.760 --> 41:09.390
Then we need a certified statement
of your revenues for the last 5 years.

41:10.520 --> 41:13.114
I'm OK sending it
with the boy, right?

41:14.160 --> 41:17.755
OK, lady. What's the cleanest way
to get this loan?

41:18.920 --> 41:20.512
Come in!

41:25.760 --> 41:26.749
Scalawags.

41:30.040 --> 41:31.553
Ýsmail Abi, they scared me.

41:32.800 --> 41:35.075
Fikret Abi, see that?

41:35.240 --> 41:37.037
How he's trained the kids?

41:37.160 --> 41:39.435
They stood up
the second we came in.

41:39.520 --> 41:41.112
Kids, selam aleykum!

41:41.280 --> 41:42.793
Thanks!

41:43.680 --> 41:44.635
Anyway.

41:44.840 --> 41:47.400
Kids, sit quietly now.
Bravo.

41:47.520 --> 41:49.397
Ýsmail Abi, what's up?
Nothing bad?

41:49.480 --> 41:51.869
Now, Saffet.
They want you at the bank.

41:52.360 --> 41:54.351
I'll explain on the way.
It's a long story.

41:54.480 --> 41:56.630
- OK, but the kids?
- I'll handle that.

41:57.480 --> 41:58.435
Take this.

41:58.640 --> 42:00.596
Go with Ýsmail Abi.
Go, Saffet.

42:01.120 --> 42:02.269
- Umm...
- C'mon.

42:02.400 --> 42:04.436
I'll handle it.
Off you go.

42:04.720 --> 42:05.709
How are you, kids?

42:05.920 --> 42:07.433
Fine thanks!

42:09.680 --> 42:11.159
Boy, is it annoying.

42:17.280 --> 42:18.633
Hey, teacher!

42:19.080 --> 42:23.232
Hey, thanks. Bless you!
What would we have done without you?

42:23.600 --> 42:25.556
Bless us all.

42:25.760 --> 42:27.478
Ýsmail Abi, we're sure to get
15,000 lira from the jewelry, huh?

42:27.600 --> 42:29.670
We'll see.
That's your job.

42:29.760 --> 42:33.196
- But you said at least 15-20,000.
- No, I didn't!

42:33.600 --> 42:34.828
That was Fikret.

42:35.440 --> 42:39.399
How do I know what I said?
I landed a gas bottle 2 days ago!

42:39.720 --> 42:41.153
I have hallucinations.

42:41.280 --> 42:43.794
Last night I saw Dad.
He was back from war in Cyprus.

42:44.640 --> 42:46.915
He said the front
needed beefing up.

42:47.000 --> 42:48.035
I said, "Do it!"

42:48.120 --> 42:49.951
"Yes, sir!" he said and left.
It's bad.

42:50.040 --> 42:51.712
The family has it rough.

42:56.480 --> 42:57.913
This sucks.

42:58.040 --> 43:01.794
Matter expands when heated,
contracts on cooling? Makes sense.

43:02.480 --> 43:03.515
Atatürk!

43:03.640 --> 43:08.156
So in which provinces did he hold
congresses? Sivas, Erzurum, Tokat and?

43:08.440 --> 43:11.079
- Amasya!
- Right.

43:11.240 --> 43:15.392
A trick question. You weren't fooled.
I've family in Tokat. My mind drifted.

43:15.560 --> 43:17.232
Never mind that.

43:17.360 --> 43:21.353
First memorize this: The foundations
of the Republic were laid in Sivas.

43:21.840 --> 43:22.795
Sit down.

43:24.120 --> 43:26.270
Çetin Abi,
why are the kids on one leg?

43:26.440 --> 43:28.158
- They're ours, teacher.
- Meaning?

43:28.320 --> 43:31.073
Call the kids at the board B-set.
B-set's a joint set.

43:31.240 --> 43:32.753
Your students and mine.

43:32.880 --> 43:36.350
The students on my course
owe fees. So I punished them.

43:36.800 --> 43:38.916
Let me hand over.

43:41.440 --> 43:42.793
Hey, listen!

43:43.160 --> 43:45.958
Wherever you are
I'll come find you.

43:46.320 --> 43:47.753
I'll get my money.

43:48.520 --> 43:49.509
Back to your place.

43:50.520 --> 43:52.078
Back to your places!

43:53.760 --> 43:56.228
One of the kids
is doing push-ups outside!

43:56.320 --> 43:59.039
He hasn't paid his fees
for 3 whole months.

43:59.320 --> 44:02.710
Standing on one foot was too easy.
Kids, I'm going.

44:02.800 --> 44:04.518
Goodbye!

44:04.880 --> 44:06.632
What did we talk about?

44:06.920 --> 44:10.515
- Selam aleykum!
- Aleykum selam!

44:10.920 --> 44:12.399
Suck on that, teacher.

44:13.520 --> 44:14.635
OK, I'm off.

44:27.560 --> 44:28.515
Agh!

44:34.320 --> 44:37.278
Oof, you didn't get my point.
This is Sivas!

44:42.840 --> 44:45.479
Where's her family?
When are they coming?

44:46.320 --> 44:49.357
I meant to tell you, dad.
There just wasn't a chance.

44:49.520 --> 44:52.273
Marika has no family.

44:53.040 --> 44:54.951
She lost her parents as a child.

44:55.120 --> 44:56.155
Poor dear.

44:56.240 --> 44:58.754
Does she have no other relatives?

44:58.880 --> 45:02.111
Aunts, uncles, whatever?
I made up all those beds.

45:02.280 --> 45:03.872
Marika has no family.

45:04.920 --> 45:08.117
She grew up in care.
The state put her through school.

45:08.440 --> 45:11.159
She needs to be among people,
you know?

45:12.040 --> 45:15.316
Now look,
what are their customs?

45:16.560 --> 45:19.791
Just like ours, dad.
It'll be just how you want it.

45:20.680 --> 45:23.638
Hah, that's.
It's easy.

45:23.800 --> 45:25.438
I'll see to that.
Now, missus.

45:25.600 --> 45:29.878
Make the guests at home.
I'm off to the teahouse.

45:30.280 --> 45:32.191
Wait, wait.
Ýsmail.

45:32.240 --> 45:33.468
What?

45:33.600 --> 45:35.955
Take this to your brother, dear.

45:36.120 --> 45:38.429
After all, he's our elder.
Here.

45:38.640 --> 45:40.995
Hey! You had invites printed?

45:41.480 --> 45:43.710
How many?
So you had money saved?

45:43.840 --> 45:45.876
What money?
These are samples.

45:46.280 --> 45:50.273
I went to the printer and told him
to print one of each, then I'd choose.

45:50.440 --> 45:51.953
Bless him, he did it.

45:52.240 --> 45:53.389
Are you...

45:54.280 --> 45:55.998
Trying to tell me something?

45:56.480 --> 45:58.675
I have four for Ýshak here.
You?

46:02.800 --> 46:06.031
- Forget what you asked, OK?
- What's he saying?

46:08.680 --> 46:10.716
Did he make her miserable?

46:10.920 --> 46:14.276
That's my girl! Now look.
Which one do you fancy?

46:14.640 --> 46:18.189
There's one with ribbon,
one with lace, everything.

46:18.440 --> 46:19.634
- Let's see.
- Look.

46:19.800 --> 46:23.076
Seeing it's an alcohol-free wedding
this is my to-do list.

46:23.360 --> 46:26.511
Well, I've done my bit.
So what about Fikret Abi?

46:27.040 --> 46:29.474
Like Ýsmail Abi said,
the girl has no family.

46:29.760 --> 46:32.274
So you know
our Nuri Abi's tea garden?

46:32.720 --> 46:35.871
I say we do it there.
Plus it'll be cool. In this heat...

46:36.480 --> 46:37.435
It'll be cool.

46:37.600 --> 46:39.875
Fikret, let's just admit it.

46:40.440 --> 46:42.351
Our first try was an epic fail.

46:43.200 --> 46:47.193
I guess your dad thought so too, Çeto.
He had no more kids after you.

46:47.480 --> 46:49.198
Once bitten, twice shy.

46:49.400 --> 46:52.039
Bravo!
That's the way to slam a guy.

46:54.440 --> 46:57.637
OK, to go from the Sivas Hotel
to the Family Tea Garden...

46:57.880 --> 46:59.359
It's a f*cker.
Anyway.

46:59.680 --> 47:02.353
Now look, Samet.
How's your side of things?

47:02.600 --> 47:03.953
It's Sermet.

47:04.920 --> 47:06.672
No, c'mon! It's Sergen.

47:06.840 --> 47:08.239
Hey, c'mon! I'm Saadet.

47:08.480 --> 47:10.675
A pleasure.
You're new in the village?

47:10.800 --> 47:12.313
What happened with your task?

47:12.440 --> 47:14.112
I tried her again today.

47:14.200 --> 47:16.509
OK, I'll say it again.
I swear she’s family.

47:16.680 --> 47:20.275
I just can't reach her.
She's at concerts, on tour.

47:20.400 --> 47:21.594
End result?

47:22.120 --> 47:23.473
The Sivas Hotel.

47:24.560 --> 47:26.152
Saadet made a dig at me, Çeto.

47:26.440 --> 47:28.351
What can I do?
It's a bummer.

47:28.400 --> 47:31.756
Someone local just qualified
for Popstar Eurostyle. I'll ask them.

47:31.800 --> 47:32.789
Great.

47:32.880 --> 47:36.509
And get some dancers from the club.
To pole dance.

47:36.880 --> 47:39.030
Sponsored by gas man Fikret.

47:41.360 --> 47:42.349
I found it funny.

47:42.640 --> 47:45.837
Ýsmail Abi, I spoke to Yilmaz
about that fake jewelry.

47:46.000 --> 47:47.558
Let's get that out the way.

47:47.720 --> 47:50.154
But it'll take an hour or two.
I say don't dally.

47:50.320 --> 47:52.595
There's no rush.
It's in Sivas, right?

47:52.800 --> 47:55.234
But not like you think.
It's a trek.

47:59.880 --> 48:01.438
Whoa!

48:01.760 --> 48:03.990
What is that?
It's like a Photoshop job.

48:04.360 --> 48:07.033
A graphic designer did that.
No architect would.

48:07.320 --> 48:08.753
Teacher, don't overdo it.

48:09.240 --> 48:11.549
Yilmaz Bey just had
precautions in mind.

48:11.920 --> 48:12.875
What precautions?

48:12.960 --> 48:15.269
Say the gendarmes raid the place.

48:16.040 --> 48:16.995
What will he do?

48:17.240 --> 48:19.754
Pour vats of boiling pitch
from up there?

48:19.920 --> 48:22.753
Fire flaming arrows?
What will he do? Huh?

48:22.960 --> 48:25.110
Ýsmail Abi,
what's with the rage?

48:25.240 --> 48:27.470
It doesn't faze the man.
What's a few steps?

48:27.680 --> 48:28.635
95!

48:28.760 --> 48:30.352
- Hah.
- I bothered to count.

48:30.880 --> 48:32.154
Çeto, I dare you.

48:32.840 --> 48:33.955
Bring Ferhat here.

48:34.200 --> 48:36.430
Tell him Shirin's waiting
up in the house.

48:36.640 --> 48:38.756
Hand him the keys
and say, "Go for it".

48:38.960 --> 48:42.669
If he can be assed to climb the steps,
lay me right here!

48:42.840 --> 48:45.035
You what?
What are you babbling about?

48:45.240 --> 48:47.959
Lay me here, roll me down.
What did you think?

48:48.040 --> 48:48.995
Oh, right.

48:49.160 --> 48:50.513
Check down below.

48:50.880 --> 48:54.111
If I'm still alive,
f*ck me, all three of you!

48:54.320 --> 48:56.914
Please! What are you saying
for God's sake?

48:57.200 --> 49:00.237
I'm picturing it.
It's too bad, me and Ýsmail Abi.

49:01.680 --> 49:03.796
Why me? Hey, why me?

49:04.720 --> 49:06.278
Don't make me crazy, Fikret!

49:06.560 --> 49:09.154
Look, I'd die anyway.
I said, if I don't die.

49:09.600 --> 49:11.272
You're all wired.

49:11.360 --> 49:15.069
Abi, you still don't get
how serious this is. Watch it!

49:15.280 --> 49:18.158
The guy up there isn't normal.
He's sick, a maniac.

49:18.280 --> 49:19.235
Just your type.

49:19.320 --> 49:20.673
Hah. Good.

49:21.440 --> 49:22.555
OK. In the name of God.

49:53.720 --> 49:56.109
Who are you? What's up?
Why are you here?

49:56.200 --> 49:59.112
No reason.
We were just passing.

49:59.680 --> 50:00.999
We're maniacs, right?

50:01.440 --> 50:03.476
Yilmaz!
We talked yesterday, right?

50:04.040 --> 50:05.758
You were gonna help us.

50:06.560 --> 50:07.788
Çeto!
Is that you?

50:07.960 --> 50:09.075
Yes, it's me.

50:09.520 --> 50:11.112
I didn't see you.
Step up front.

50:11.560 --> 50:12.515
Out of the way.

50:13.160 --> 50:14.388
Come in, c'mon.

50:19.280 --> 50:20.315
Mister...

50:20.640 --> 50:23.200
Did you build this lair up here...

50:23.520 --> 50:26.956
So we'd have time to think on the way
if we were getting cold feet?

50:27.320 --> 50:30.039
I just wasted my last breath
asking that question.

50:30.840 --> 50:33.229
I'm about to pass out.
Here goes.

50:33.720 --> 50:34.948
Oh my God, Fikret Abi!

50:35.600 --> 50:40.720
Fikret? Fikret!
Hey, did you pass out, Fikret?

50:41.480 --> 50:44.870
See that? If I pass out now,
they'll think I'm aping him.

50:45.320 --> 50:46.639
Too bad!

50:47.120 --> 50:49.554
You'd think there's no girls
in the village!

50:52.800 --> 50:54.392
Marsiye!
C'mon, we're going.

50:54.560 --> 50:57.233
Marsiye? Mum, that's a TV soap.
Her name’s Marika.

50:57.320 --> 51:00.790
Maybe it is, but my name's Hatice.
Nothing to be done.

51:01.000 --> 51:06.235
Tell her to come with us.
Say, "You're going with Mum and co".

51:07.440 --> 51:10.159
OK, Mum. I do speak Turkish.
For goodness sake!

51:15.760 --> 51:17.716
- Going where?
- Is Miss Mahpeyker asking?

51:17.880 --> 51:20.235
God, is it Mahpeyker now?
No, I'm asking.

51:20.520 --> 51:22.238
To drink soda!
God!

51:23.560 --> 51:25.551
C'mon then, let's do it!

51:27.000 --> 51:29.150
Oh my, look at you and that belly!

51:30.640 --> 51:32.995
Over here, dear.
C'mon, dance.

51:34.360 --> 51:36.032
OK, time to feed the girls.

51:37.120 --> 51:38.439
Here, honey.

51:39.120 --> 51:40.348
What, what?

51:40.440 --> 51:42.829
Here.
C'mon now, eat!

51:45.080 --> 51:46.479
Oh my God!

51:53.280 --> 51:56.158
So this isn't the way
to eat everything.

51:57.160 --> 51:58.752
Health is everything, dear.

52:06.760 --> 52:07.954
That isn't tap water.

52:08.120 --> 52:09.553
No, purified.
Made it myself.

52:09.640 --> 52:11.676
God knows what goes
in the tap water.

52:11.800 --> 52:12.869
Gotta purify it.

52:12.960 --> 52:13.949
God is great!

52:14.040 --> 52:15.393
No deliveries, huh?

52:15.520 --> 52:17.431
Who'd haul
5-gallon bottles up 95 steps?

52:17.560 --> 52:20.757
I wouldn't bring gas.
Delivery guys are human too.

52:20.960 --> 52:23.997
If I lived here, I'd never get bread.
I'd die of hunger.

52:24.120 --> 52:25.519
I make bread myself.

52:28.360 --> 52:29.634
Fikret Abi, OK.

52:29.800 --> 52:32.268
The trek here did you in.
Don't overdo it.

52:33.840 --> 52:34.795
Yilmaz!

52:34.920 --> 52:38.037
Aren't businesses like this
meant to be in basements?

52:39.440 --> 52:42.591
Son, we almost died
coming up those steps.

52:42.840 --> 52:45.035
How did you find it?
You were ripped off, son.

52:45.320 --> 52:46.275
Son?

52:48.080 --> 52:50.878
Run! Run for it, run!

52:53.000 --> 52:53.989
What's up with him?

52:54.200 --> 52:55.428
I'd be wrong to say.

52:55.880 --> 52:57.916
Yilmaz, it's OK.
A glass took a tumble.

52:58.120 --> 52:59.917
- Çeto, is that you?
- Yes.

53:03.280 --> 53:06.875
Then I'll take you all to the workshop
where I do my R&D.

53:07.040 --> 53:07.995
R&D?

53:10.240 --> 53:11.639
Faruk, talk to the girl.

53:11.840 --> 53:13.193
She calls your mum
Hatice Haným.

53:13.280 --> 53:16.795
Only your dad calls her 'missus'.
It upsets the woman.

53:17.240 --> 53:20.516
Please, Þengül Teyze.
She only has a few words of Turkish.

53:20.640 --> 53:22.676
Let her say what she likes.
Is 'Abla' better?

53:23.560 --> 53:25.312
You have your work cut out, dear.

53:25.440 --> 53:27.954
Once we're back in Istanbul
after the wedding...

53:28.040 --> 53:30.270
We'll only visit
once or twice a year.

53:30.320 --> 53:31.594
Istanbul?

53:31.800 --> 53:33.677
Isn't the firm abroad?

53:35.240 --> 53:38.550
Sure it is,
but we won't always be there.

53:38.640 --> 53:40.949
It works by appointment.
When they have the staff...

53:41.160 --> 53:43.196
Even the water,
it's like watery soda.

53:43.280 --> 53:46.397
So like, it's 7.00 there now.
Mum, what kept you so long?

53:46.560 --> 53:49.074
A skirt down to my knees
barely covers her bum.

53:49.200 --> 53:53.113
So I've no idea what she got.
But I did see two G-strings.

53:53.480 --> 53:54.833
Shame on you, Mum!

53:54.920 --> 53:57.036
Why? Does she understand
for heaven's sake?

53:57.120 --> 53:58.997
C'mon, let's go.
You as well.

54:04.440 --> 54:05.395
Hey!

54:05.880 --> 54:07.996
- Isn't that Ahmet Özhan? Wow!
- Fikret.

54:10.040 --> 54:12.679
The gold's here.
You'd never know it's fake.

54:12.920 --> 54:15.673
There's double-hardened steel
under the plating.

54:16.200 --> 54:17.997
It won't break, bend or buckle.

54:18.160 --> 54:22.199
It's a bit heavier than normal steel.
Here, feel the weight.

54:22.960 --> 54:26.316
- Yilmaz, we also need a camel.
- Haunch or fillet?

54:26.400 --> 54:28.789
No, not to eat.
For riding.

54:29.880 --> 54:32.269
I'll fix it.
I'll fix it, God willing.

54:33.920 --> 54:35.478
Weren't you an only child?

54:35.600 --> 54:38.273
Yilmaz looks so like you.
Are you brothers?

54:38.520 --> 54:40.351
That's an insult!
Brothers?

54:40.440 --> 54:42.874
Like my mum would give birth
to anything so ugly.

54:43.200 --> 54:45.998
If she shat,
it would be prettier.

54:46.080 --> 54:47.593
You only had to say no.

54:47.720 --> 54:48.709
What can I do, teacher?

54:49.000 --> 54:50.638
There's nothing I can't do.

54:50.880 --> 54:52.313
Oh God!

54:56.640 --> 54:59.552
I forged banknotes
not even ATMs could pick out.

54:59.760 --> 55:02.274
I sent the Central Bank some.
They were amazed.

55:02.960 --> 55:06.430
I was expecting an engraved plaque.
They gave me 4 years.

55:06.560 --> 55:07.549
If only you'd refused.

55:08.560 --> 55:09.709
Can you do that?

55:10.760 --> 55:12.079
No, you can't.

55:12.640 --> 55:13.755
Right.

55:14.000 --> 55:15.035
I'll find that camel.

55:17.120 --> 55:19.395
He's so like my late dad.

55:21.880 --> 55:23.438
Did you call me 'son'?

55:23.760 --> 55:24.715
No.

55:26.600 --> 55:27.999
It's as good as real.

55:28.360 --> 55:29.509
Where's technology going?

55:29.960 --> 55:33.236
He said not even ATMs could tell
his fake notes. Didn't you hear?

55:33.360 --> 55:35.476
If only we'd shelled out a bit more...

55:35.560 --> 55:39.314
And not got the cheap stuff.
This isn't great, Ýsmail Abi.

55:39.480 --> 55:40.435
Is it so obvious?

55:40.480 --> 55:43.233
I know lira notes
to have Atatürk's face on them.

55:43.400 --> 55:46.073
But this has
a full-length portrait.

55:47.360 --> 55:48.349
Give it here, Çeto.

55:49.960 --> 55:51.598
It's a full-length portrait.

55:52.000 --> 55:54.230
Not Atatürk either.
It's Kazým Karabekir.

55:55.520 --> 55:57.715
Mental Bank of Turkey.

56:01.280 --> 56:03.475
Ýsmail Abi, what's up?
Something's not OK.

56:03.600 --> 56:05.830
No. Just an important errand to do.

56:06.680 --> 56:09.433
I'll be back in half an hour.
I'll explain then.

56:09.840 --> 56:11.432
- Where's he going?
- How do I know?

56:31.320 --> 56:33.515
Weddings or funerals
are no place for bad blood.

56:35.840 --> 56:37.353
That's what I was taught.

56:37.440 --> 56:40.159
But invites don't go
to close family either.

56:40.360 --> 56:41.315
In the old days...

56:42.800 --> 56:46.713
People knew if they were in favor
from whether they got an invite.

56:47.360 --> 56:48.713
If you gave anyone invites...

56:50.520 --> 56:52.715
They'd get upset
and boycott the wedding.

56:53.160 --> 56:56.869
"Invited to our own wedding?"
They'd say, and refuse to go.

57:00.320 --> 57:03.517
Here, brother.
It's your invite.

57:05.720 --> 57:08.837
I'm your junior.
I've come to you out of respect.

57:10.680 --> 57:13.114
I got beyond
who's right and wrong.

57:14.240 --> 57:17.152
Brother, you're the only elder
in my boy's family.

57:18.160 --> 57:22.438
Read him a verse of the Koran.
Put a ring on his finger.

57:23.640 --> 57:25.995
Then let's dance like real men.

57:26.440 --> 57:28.158
For everyone to see.

57:37.560 --> 57:40.074
.
Preparations can start!

58:18.480 --> 58:19.435
There you go!

58:19.520 --> 58:23.069
THE BRIDE'S SIDE
LATVIA

58:29.280 --> 58:32.397
I called so many times, baby.
Why don't you answer?

58:32.680 --> 58:35.831
I didn't hear, honey.
It's kind of noisy here.

58:36.560 --> 58:38.312
The reception sucks anyway.

58:38.440 --> 58:40.795
Where exactly are you, baby?
I'm curious.

58:40.880 --> 58:42.393
In a village near Sivas.

58:42.880 --> 58:44.757
The wedding's tonight.
In a field.

58:45.000 --> 58:46.592
The name of Tank's village?

58:47.200 --> 58:49.634
It's called Esenyurt.

58:50.720 --> 58:53.439
Did Marika's family find out?
Are they mad?

58:53.880 --> 58:58.590
Well.
I guess they're a bit upset.

59:01.040 --> 59:03.759
We only escaped
thanks to you, babe.

59:03.920 --> 59:04.955
Rubbish.

59:05.200 --> 59:09.796
Nothing would've stopped you.
I didn't do anything.

59:10.160 --> 59:13.152
No way, honey.
You even paid for our flights.

59:13.240 --> 59:17.199
You took Marika's brothers out that night.
You did everything, my hero.

59:18.560 --> 59:23.475
No, stop.
You're playing with the truth.

59:23.760 --> 59:25.398
Honey, I'm hanging up.

59:25.880 --> 59:29.350
We forgot the chargers.
We could get cut off any second.

59:29.600 --> 59:31.511
How could you forget the chargers?

59:36.440 --> 59:38.237
You had it coming, Viktors.

59:43.160 --> 59:45.880
If we get there before
the marriage vows...

59:45.880 --> 59:49.350
...we can rescue the girl
and return her to her fiancé.

59:49.520 --> 59:55.390
And we'll spare your life
for helping us.

59:56.600 --> 01:00:00.673
If we don't get there in time,
her fiancé will kill you.

01:00:00.880 --> 01:00:02.791
Go, get there before the wedding.

01:00:07.640 --> 01:00:09.358
What are you waiting for?

01:00:09.640 --> 01:00:13.997
C'mon, run.
Get to the village before them.

01:00:14.600 --> 01:00:17.520
If those boys crash the
wedding, there'll be carnage.

01:00:17.520 --> 01:00:19.829
Better just you die
than a mass of people.

01:00:20.560 --> 01:00:22.118
I'll slowly get going then.

01:00:33.080 --> 01:00:35.435
Switch them on!

01:00:42.720 --> 01:00:45.712
Oh my God!
We're talking dynamite.

01:00:46.000 --> 01:00:47.956
Hey, the camel's here!

01:00:48.960 --> 01:00:50.359
The camel's here.

01:00:51.280 --> 01:00:53.077
- Tarik, Tarik!
- Yes, Dad?

01:00:53.240 --> 01:00:56.198
Get up, son. The camel's here.
Look, the camel's here.

01:00:56.280 --> 01:00:58.396
Where did they find it?

01:00:58.680 --> 01:00:59.999
My God.

01:01:02.400 --> 01:01:04.595
Atta boy! Good work!

01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:08.151
Just look at that, look at you.
Magnificent!

01:01:08.480 --> 01:01:12.189
Bravo, my boy.
What a beauty of a camel.

01:01:12.320 --> 01:01:13.833
- Abi, what is this?
- A camel?

01:01:13.920 --> 01:01:15.751
Is this a joke, Çetin Abi?

01:01:15.880 --> 01:01:20.078
I said the same myself,
but your dad insists it's a tradition.

01:01:20.240 --> 01:01:24.597
The bride will climb on that camel
and ride from the house to the wedding.

01:01:24.840 --> 01:01:26.034
It's a tradition with us.

01:01:26.120 --> 01:01:28.270
A tradition with you?
Who are you?

01:01:28.680 --> 01:01:32.070
I never heard of it.
I didn't ride a camel as a bride.

01:01:32.320 --> 01:01:35.630
Missus, you were rounder then.
We felt sorry for the camel.

01:01:36.080 --> 01:01:40.278
Ýsmail, the girl can't ride a camel.
She's educated.

01:01:40.440 --> 01:01:41.998
How'd she know about your traditions?

01:01:42.200 --> 01:01:45.715
Hear that? I said "your" traditions.
We have nothing like that.

01:01:45.840 --> 01:01:48.957
Ýsmail Abi!
Ýsmail Abi. Wait for this!

01:01:49.080 --> 01:01:51.878
What's up, teacher?
Did you mess up again?

01:01:52.160 --> 01:01:53.388
No, nothing's wrong.

01:01:53.480 --> 01:01:54.515
Was that a camel?

01:01:55.520 --> 01:01:56.475
God, it is.

01:01:56.640 --> 01:01:57.914
Çeto, what's this?

01:01:58.240 --> 01:01:59.195
A camel.

01:01:59.320 --> 01:02:00.878
Are you taking the piss?
Dick!

01:02:01.040 --> 01:02:03.793
God! Ýsmail Abi said get it,
so I got it.

01:02:03.880 --> 01:02:06.269
Why's everyone laying into me?

01:02:06.400 --> 01:02:07.628
Quiet boy, quiet girl.

01:02:07.760 --> 01:02:09.716
My man's just invented
a new tradition.

01:02:09.920 --> 01:02:12.593
The bride rides a camel
to the wedding!

01:02:12.760 --> 01:02:14.432
Weren't you welcoming guests?

01:02:14.600 --> 01:02:16.477
OK, remember the lights we put up?

01:02:16.680 --> 01:02:18.591
What, the big colored things?

01:02:18.760 --> 01:02:20.239
The big colored ones.

01:02:23.680 --> 01:02:27.468
(Meaningless gabble)

01:02:38.560 --> 01:02:41.870
If you don't know camel language,
don't confuse the beast.

01:02:42.080 --> 01:02:46.437
Abi, the lights blew the fuses.
Tarik knows about electrics, right?

01:02:46.680 --> 01:02:50.514
Tarik. C'mon, please, son.
Go take a look at them.

01:02:50.800 --> 01:02:53.473
But be careful.
Don't get that suit dirty.

01:02:53.680 --> 01:02:55.955
Hey, Çeto!
Bring the camel over.

01:02:56.120 --> 01:02:57.473
Still on his camel trip.

01:02:58.480 --> 01:03:00.357
God help us!

01:03:00.480 --> 01:03:02.471
Broke and going to the wedding
by camel!

01:03:03.280 --> 01:03:04.713
<i>And so we did.</i>

01:03:04.920 --> 01:03:08.037
<i>We went on ahead.
I fixed the fuses and put them back.</i>

01:03:08.240 --> 01:03:09.719
<i>Twice I nearly died.</i>

01:03:10.200 --> 01:03:12.794
<i>We felt sure
the disasters were now over.</i>

01:03:13.320 --> 01:03:14.992
<i>But turns out that was hasty.</i>

01:03:15.720 --> 01:03:17.756
Where did you get this camel?

01:03:19.160 --> 01:03:21.310
Look at that smile.
I know you.

01:03:21.560 --> 01:03:24.950
C'mon, I won't tell.
Who did you nick it from?

01:03:25.280 --> 01:03:28.875
I didn't, I borrowed it.
Ýsmail Abi didn't pay a cent either.

01:03:29.200 --> 01:03:32.192
He said it was tradition,
he wanted a camel, so I got one.

01:03:32.520 --> 01:03:34.431
- I shouldn't have?
- Get out of here!

01:03:34.520 --> 01:03:36.590
It's not like taking a bike
for a spin.

01:03:36.640 --> 01:03:38.278
Borrow a camel?
My ass!

01:03:38.440 --> 01:03:41.113
- Çeto, what's on the camel's butt?
- Oh God!

01:03:41.200 --> 01:03:42.599
How do I know, Fikret Abi?

01:03:42.920 --> 01:03:45.229
Why keep asking me about the camel?

01:03:45.440 --> 01:03:47.795
Looks like a tick, Çeto.

01:03:48.720 --> 01:03:53.874
If it's a tick, get behind the beast,
grab the thing and pull it off!

01:03:54.200 --> 01:03:55.189
Boy!

01:03:55.280 --> 01:03:56.793
- Çeto, what did you do?
- Çeto!

01:03:56.960 --> 01:03:58.109
- Çeto, do something!
- Çeto!

01:03:58.280 --> 01:04:00.191
Get off my back!
Don't give me grief!

01:04:00.360 --> 01:04:03.158
He brought the camel.
Why are you blaming me?

01:04:03.280 --> 01:04:04.759
Do I run a camel farm?

01:04:04.840 --> 01:04:06.671
Boys. You know what?

01:04:07.080 --> 01:04:09.548
The bride's snatched the camel!
Run! Run!

01:04:09.640 --> 01:04:10.993
- Hey!
- Run!

01:04:12.040 --> 01:04:15.396
Çeto, I'm off to the wedding then.
You do the chasing.

01:04:15.640 --> 01:04:16.595
Thanks.

01:04:20.600 --> 01:04:23.114
No panic.
We'll have a great time.

